-- BofA-ML Increases 2011 Copper Forecast to $11,250 From $8,000 a Metric Ton
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2010-11-11T06:55:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/bofa-ml-increases-2011-copper-forecast-to-11-250-from-8-000-a-metric-ton.html
Copper will rise to $11,250 a metric
ton next year, up from a previous forecast of $8,000, Bank of
America Merrill Lynch said in a report.  Copper, zinc, silver, platinum and thermal coal are the
“preferred commodity exposures,”  BofA-ML analyst Jason
Fairclough wrote in a report dated today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  